MALE (n= 5
). Smaller than female, 152–172, 47 – 52 wide. Gnathosoma 23–25 , basal seta ( ep ) 2–3 , apical seta ( d ) 11–12 , chelicerae 16–18 . Prodorsal shield same/similar to female, 52–54, 42 – 49 wide. Scapular setae ( sc ) 5–7 on tubercles, 29–32 apart. Frontal lobe 14–18, 22 – 26 wide. Legs same/similar to female.
